sub_title: VP of Engineering, EMEA, Sage + Archer \ Vistar Media
summary:
24AM is the mobile first creative & media agency that reaches and activates people. We do so with a contemporary perspective on consumer behaviour and digital media opportunities. 24AM translates a brand’s digital ambition into a strategy, creative concept and mobile first media approach in order to grow brand performance.

Late 2011 Edwin started MobPro (Mobile Professionals) together with two other experienced internet marketing professionals. With our collective knowledge and network we help advertisers reach their mobile advertising goals. So far we have run more than 1500 mobile marketing campaigns in the Netherlands, France, Belgium, Sweden and the UK. We have created and launched the first European mobile-only DSP and manage the complete mobile marketing campaign for many companies.

Edwin has experience as a consultant, project manager and entrepreneur in the area of intelligent search technologies, internet and e-business. He holds degrees in Psychology and Social Computer Science from the University of Amsterdam.

Edwin joined the KaZaA team in 2000, focusing on meta-data, user experience and product development. Next to that he worked on addition licensing and implementing the FastTrack protocol which is the predecessor of the technology that was at the core of Skype.

Since January 2007 Edwin worked as Information Officer at M4N, optimising the business in any conceivable way. He worked on technological and organisational aspects as well as process optimisation in his role as member of the MT. The company has won a lot of prices in fast growing companies lists, so that worked out quite well. In 2011 M4N was acquired by Zanox, the leading performance based network in Europe.
